    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Prodrome of\nheadache\n, malaise, photophobia,\nfever\nUnilateral\npain\nor hypesthesia in V1 distribution\nHyperemic\nconjunctivitis\n,\nepiscleritis\n, lid droop\nVesicular\nrash\nin V1 distribution\nSlit-lamp exam\n:\nInitial finding of punctate epithelial keratitis that then evolves into pseudodendrite\n[1]\nPseudodendrite (poorly staining mucous plaque with no epithelial erosion)\nIn contrast to\nHSV\nwhich has true dendrite with epithelial erosion and staining\nCell and flare",
      "subsections": {},
